  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Early childhood development for Venezuelan refugees and host communities in poor urban areas of Lima</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Warmi Huasi will strengthen two community-run centres, one in Carabayllo and one in San Martin de Porres (the district where most Venezuelans currently reside). They will train 30 community volunteers to run these centres which will act as hubs and will link up with state-run services to provide the following vital services for the communities they serve: education to 100 Venezuelan and Peruvian mothers, fathers and other family members on health issues, nutrition and parenting skills for 100 children under 5; monitor the children&#x2019;s growth and nutritional status; opportunities for early learning through play and participation in well-being clubs; and additional nutritional support and psychosocial services to overcome trauma and abuse for Venezuelan children. By working with both Venezuelan refugee/migrant and host communities, this project will also overcome the isolation, stigma and discrimination that many Venezuelan families are facing and integrate them into the local community.</narrative>
  </description>
